summary: Help me find a post please?

Help me find a post please?

There was a headcanon post going around a while ago that kind of went “what if Aziraphale’s name was originally ‘Aziraphael’, in keeping with how you spell&pronounce Raphael and other angel names of the kind, but because of its divine nature Crowley can’t say it and this is why he changed it around a little bit.”

I was so sure I reblogged it but now I can’t find it anywhere and I need it because of Reasons!

summary: Because I finally saw Detective Pikachu, some Pokemon headcannons: Crowley has an Ekans, Aziraphale a Starly. Aziraphale was...
caption:
Because I finally saw Detective Pikachu, some Pokemon headcannons:

Crowley has an Ekans, Aziraphale a Starly. Aziraphale was resistant to getting a Pokemon at all - books and animals don’t mix - but he found Starly with a broken wing, and upon healing it, the bird Pokemon wouldn’t leave him alone. Starly turns out to be quite good at fetching books for Aziraphale from the highest shelves, and is very careful with the pages, so their partnership works out quite nicely. Crowley, meanwhile, wanted a Pokemon from the get-go, and Ekans was an obvious choice. The snake Pokemon likes to drape itself around his shoulders (even when it starts getting too big for it). It also likes licking Aziraphale.
